Problem Statement: Amateur singers who post cover songs on TikTok struggle to build a cohesive, visually appealing presence — especially when posting anonymously. There's no easy way to quickly generate a consistent aesthetic, matching captions, and hashtag strategy for each cover post without spending hours on research and design. Cover Creator Studio solves this by letting a user describe a song or vibe and instantly receive a tailored creative package for their TikTok post.


Target User: A college-aged, creative individual who:
- Records and posts song covers on TikTok (anonymously or otherwise)
- Uses tools like GarageBand to produce their audio
- Has a graphic design eye but wants faster output
- Wants their TikTok page to feel cohesive and intentional without a huge time investment
- Is building a personal brand around music without necessarily revealing their identity


MUST HAVES (MVP — v1):
1. Song & Vibe Input

A simple input form where the user enters:
- Song title and original artist
- Their intended mood or spin on the cover (e.g., "soft and emotional," "upbeat and fun," "dark and moody")

2. Aesthetic Mood Board Generator

Based on the song and vibe input, the app returns:
- A color palette (3–5 hex colors that match the vibe)
- A vibe description (2–3 sentences describing the visual mood)
- Font style suggestions (e.g., "handwritten and soft" or "bold and editorial")
- Visual direction tip (e.g., "think warm candlelight, close-up shots, minimal movement")

3. TikTok Caption & Hashtag Generator
The app returns a ready-to-use TikTok post package:

- A short, engaging caption (fits TikTok's style — punchy, relatable, no fluff)
- 10–15 relevant hashtags (mix of niche and broad for reach)
- An optional anonymous-friendly CTA (e.g., "drop your favorite lyric below 👇")


USER INTERACTION:
1. User lands on the app homepage
        ↓
2. User fills out the input form:
   - Song title + original artist
   - Their mood/spin on the cover
        ↓
3. User clicks "Generate My Vibe"
        ↓
4. AI processes the input and returns:
   - Mood board (color palette + vibe description + font tips + visual direction)
   - TikTok caption + hashtags + CTA
        ↓
5. User reviews output on a clean results screen
        ↓
6. User copies what they need and posts their cover
        ↓
7. Optional: User clicks "Start Over" to generate for a new song
